Source: ffmpeg-pistomp
Section: video
Priority: optional
Maintainer: pistomp <pistomp@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), nasm, pkgconf,
 libx264-dev, libvorbis-dev, libogg-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: ffmpeg-pistomp
Architecture: arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Provides: ffmpeg
Conflicts: ffmpeg
Replaces: ffmpeg
Description: Minimal ffmpeg build for pi-Stomp
 A stripped-down ffmpeg build intended for pi-Stomp's ps-record-lcd
 utility. Supports rawvideo input and H.264 (libx264) output to MP4,
 plus Vorbis decoding, without any SDL2, X11, OpenGL, PulseAudio,
 ALSA, network protocols, or other display/audio-output device
 dependencies.
